{code}

h1. so...
Tildes as escape character is described in [PreformattedAndNowiki|http://www.wikicreole.org/wiki/PreformattedAndNowiki].

These strange behaviours are very trivial, and even though they are obviously bug, the fix of those might destroy many written contents, so don&#x27;t fix without loudly announcement, please.

When using Oauth1 authentification,all calls to the following APIs fail with "This endpoint does not support token-based authentication".

* https://bitbucket.org/api/2.0/users/{name}
* https://bitbucket.org/api/2.0/teams/{name}

My collaborator posted a link in the comment to the issue with link text (in Unicode) and reference (url) -  it looks in the browser like

{code}
#!html
<a href="https://github.com/moodle/moodle/blob/master/question/type/edit_question_form.php#L328">Вот</a>
{code}

However when I get this comment by e-mail, the text and the reference were reversed: the text of the link become a reference and the reference become a text:

{code}
#!html
<a href="http://%D0%92%D0%BE%D1%82" style="color:#3572b0;text-decoration:none" target="_blank">https://github.com/moodle/<wbr>moodle/blob/master/question/<wbr>type/edit_question_form.php#<wbr>L328</a>
{code}

With git, it&#x27;s possible to push two branches to the same repo and then to create a "fake" PR between them (fake because nothing is getting pulled, it&#x27;s more a "merge request" than a "pull request").

With hg, if you push two heads on the same named branch, you can&#x27;t do the same, even if you identify each head by a bookmark. Everything seems to work fine at first. You can even see which commits bb thinks would be merged into the target head, but if you attempt to save the PR, bb errors out with

{code}
The following error(s) occurred saving this pull request

    There are no changes to be pulled
{code}
